      "role": "user",
      "content": "i've seen a lot of reports saying that relying on just solar and wind is basically a pipe dream if we want to avoid a complete collapse. like, if we don't commit to massive nuclear expansion right now, we're basically just choosing to fail. is it actually possible to ignore nuclear energy and still hit our targets, or is that just unrealistic talk?",
